      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 116: `factor \u003d 1.0f - congestion * cfg_.maxDecreaseFactor` makes `maxDecreaseFactor` behave as the maximum reduction, but the subsequent clamp is fragile and the defaults are not validated against the increase factors. If `minIncreaseFactor \u003e maxIncreaseFactor` is configured, probing can produce negative or inverted ramp behavior. Normalize these related factors in the constructor so the controller cannot be misconfigured into decreasing while probing.\n```suggestion\ncfg_.minIncreaseFactor \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.minIncreaseFactor, 0.0f, 1.0f);\ncfg_.maxIncreaseFactor \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.maxIncreaseFactor, 0.0f, 1.0f);\nif (cfg_.minIncreaseFactor \u003e cfg_.maxIncreaseFactor)\n    std::swap(cfg_.minIncreaseFactor, cfg_.maxIncreaseFactor);\n```",
