      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 673: Calling `setNewBitrate()` for every RTCP RR update now calls `bwController_.setTargetBitrate(newBR)`, and `setTargetBitrate()` resets `lastStableBitrate_` to the just-applied bitrate. After a congestion decrease this immediately overwrites the pre-congestion recovery reference, so the controller can lose its intended recovery ceiling and AIMD state. Split the API into an external/manual target setter and an applied-bitrate sync that only clamps `targetBitrate_` without changing `lastStableBitrate_`.\n```suggestion\n// bandwidth_controller.h\nvoid syncAppliedBitrate(unsigned bitrateKbps);\n\n// bandwidth_controller.cpp\nvoid\nBandwidthController::syncAppliedBitrate(unsigned bitrateKbps)\n{\n    std::lock_guard lock(mutex_);\n    targetBitrate_ \u003d clampBitrate(bitrateKbps);\n}\n\n// video_rtp_session.cpp\nbwController_.syncAppliedBitrate(newBR);\n```",
