      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 865: `delayMonitor()` writes REMB packets through `socketPair_` from the RTP delay callback without taking the session mutex, while `start()`/teardown can reset `socketPair_`. The null check does not protect against a concurrent reset after the check, which can lead to use-after-free. Take a stable local shared/locked reference using the same synchronization pattern used elsewhere for `socketPair_`, or guard this callback with the session mutex before dereferencing.\n```suggestion\nstd::lock_guard lock(mutex_);\nif (!socketPair_)\n    return;\n...\nsocketPair_-\u003ewriteData(v.data(), static_cast\u003cint\u003e(v.size()));\n```",
